&lt;h2&gt;Staff Nurse&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ambitious, motivated and passionate about nursing?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a real difference to every one of your patients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work in a clinical area where no two days are the same?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the answer to these is yes – then D7 would love you to share our commitment to excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;D7 are currently going through an exciting period of change. However, our ultimate goal will continue to be ensuring our patients receive the highest standard of care. We are a highly skilled team that learns and develops together, providing holistic care for a variety of acute and complex patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love you to join our team and share our commitment to providing excellent standards of nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest NHS trusts in the country, we provide acute and specialist services for almost a million people throughout Portsmouth and South East Hampshire, employing c7,000 staff and generating an annual income in excess of £410m. We continue to build our reputation for innovation and excellence, consistently delivering outstanding performance, whilst developing the skills and abilities of our staff as we go.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So why not join us, and you can look forward to all the scope and support you need to achieve your professional goals in this progressive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits prior to interview are welcome, please contact Sefora Melo on 02392 286000 EXT 6840.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 25/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
